    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nwhen nvim_win_get_buf() gets called in a callback of `WinEnter` event, it returns incorrect value.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. nvim --clean +'luafile test.lua'\r\n2. `:q`, `:q`\r\n\r\nat step 1, messages can be seen as:\r\n```\r\nwin=1002, winbuf=1, curbuf=1                                                    \r\nwin=1003, winbuf=2, curbuf=2\r\n```\r\n\r\nafter step 2, messages can be seen as (via `:mes`):\r\n```\r\nwin=1002, winbuf=1, curbuf=1                                                    \r\nwin=1003, winbuf=2, curbuf=2\r\nwin=1002, winbuf=2, curbuf=2\r\nwin=1000, winbuf=1, curbuf=1\r\n```\r\n\r\ntest.lua\r\n```lua\r\nlocal api = vim.api\r\n\r\nlocal b1 = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nlocal b2 = api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\n\r\napi.nvim_create_autocmd(\"winenter\", {\r\n  callback = function()\r\n    local winid = api.nvim_get_current_win()\r\n    local curbufnr = api.nvim_get_current_buf()\r\n    local bufnr = api.nvim_win_get_buf(winid)\r\n    print(string.format(\"win=%d, winbuf=%d, curbuf=%d\", winid, bufnr, curbufnr))\r\n  end,\r\n})\r\n\r\nlocal width = math.floor(vim.go.columns / 3)\r\nlocal height = math.floor(vim.go.lines / 3)\r\n\r\n-- stylua: ignore\r\napi.nvim_open_win(b1, true, {\r\n  relative = \"editor\", border = \"single\", width = width, height = height,\r\n  row = 0, col = 0,\r\n  title = \"w1+\"..b1,\r\n})\r\n\r\n-- stylua: ignore\r\napi.nvim_open_win(b2, true, {\r\n  relative = \"editor\", border = \"single\", width = width, height = height,\r\n  row = 5, col = 5,\r\n  title = \"w2+\"..b2,\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nnvim_win_get_buf and nvim_get_current_buf return correct value.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\narchlinux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nst 0.9\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nst-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nsystem package manager",
